> A zesty blend of spices, garlic, and fresh herbs, chermoula is a Moroccan spice traditionally used to season fish and meat, and is the hero seasoning in tonight's speedy dish. Sweet juicy prawns in a thick tomato sauce packed with fresh veggies and served alongside roasted sweet potatoes, it's hard to say which ingredient we love most. Regardless of the weather outside, this recipe will transport you to the warm, sunny climes of Northern Africa.

== Couscous ==

Pour the @water{300%ml} into a #measuring jug{}. Add the @chicken stock powder{1/2%tsp} and stir to dissolve.

Pop the @couscous{150%g} into a #bowl{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pour in the boiling stock and cover
the bowl with #plate{}. Leave to one side for ~{8%minutes}, the couscous will absorb the water and swell up in this time.

== Prep ==

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1} then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Chop the @lemon{1/2} into wedges.

Drain the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

== Chermoula Sauce ==

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the courgette and cook stirring
frequently for ~{2%minutes}.

Add the @chermoula spice mix{1} and stir in, cook for ~{1%minute} and then add the @chopped tomatoes{1}(finely chopped with onion and garlic)
and the @water{100%ml}.

== Prawns ==

Add the @king prawns{120} and chickpeas to the sauce. Lower the heat to medium.

Simmer until the prawns are cooked and the courgettes are soft, ~{3-4%minutes}, stirring every now and then.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

== Assembly ==

Fluff the couscous up with a #fork{} and stir in half the coriander and a squeeze of lemon juice.

Taste and add salt and pepper if required.

Share the couscous between your #bowls{}. Top with the chermoula prawns.

Add a wedge of lemon and finish with a sprinkling of the remaining coriander.